{"questionId":"27853","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A cat runs inside a circular exercise wheel, making the wheel spin at a constant rate in an&nbsp;anticlockwise direction. The height, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo> </mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>, of a fixed point, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>, on the wheel can be modelled&nbsp;by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math> where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is the time in seconds and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/7de117abb218e40ac8e77b30edf45ee9032cd592.png\"></p>\n<p>When <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math> is at a height of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>78</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>When <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>, point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math> first reaches its maximum height of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>143</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Later, the cat is tired, and it takes twice as long for point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math> to complete one revolution at&nbsp;a new constant rate.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the new value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>196</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>196349</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>16</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27853","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.12d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the new value of b.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}